Examples of Verbs giving evidence of different (cognitive) activities are shown (as a hierarchy) below. 

(Not comprehensive or necessarily correct -a 'model' for guidance)
Verbs giving evidence of - 
Knowledge - 
Describe, outline, name, reproduce, recall, select, state, present, organise, recognise, recount, write, measure, know  (Describe) 
Comprehension - 
Interpret, translate, comprehend, clarify, defend, explain, discuss, report, identify, indicate, select, contrast, compare, classify  (Compare] 
